SCOPE
Request the development of a Pharmacy Management System (PMS) to modernize the traditional pharmacy
operations currently dependent on manual registers, paper-based billing, inconsistent stock management
methods, and non-integrated invoicing systems.
• A complete POS-driven medication billing system
• Centralized inventory with batch, expiry, and MRP tracking
• Supplier and purchase order management
• Customer and membership management
• Printer and label QR/barcode configuration
• Multi-branch operations
• Advanced reporting and auditing functionality
The PMS eliminates the limitations associated with paper systems, reduces human error, enables real-time
pharmaceutical compliance, and supports rapid, accurate pharmacy operations.
Four core concepts are encompassed within the system’s general scope:
1. Replacement of paper-based billing with a digital POS
2. Centralized batch-wise inventory and expiry tracking
3. Supplier, purchase, and inward stock digitalization
4. A robust store-wise admin panel for pharmacy supervision
This document focuses on the software, its internal and external interfaces, expected behavior, and interactions
among users, systems, and modules.
1.1 OVERVIEW
The Pharmacy Management System is a modern, responsive, MERN-based application designed to streamline
all workflows of standalone and multi-branch pharmacies. It covers user registration, inventory onboarding,
supplier management, store configuration, medicine purchase entry, POS billing, and reporting analytics.
The PMS ensures:
• Accurate batch-wise medicine dispensing
• Automatic stock reconciliation
• Integration with QR/Barcode printers
• High-level compliance with pharmaceutical sales laws
• Role-based access for store staff
• Real-time GST computation
The system includes full activity logging, audit trails, and error-handling mechanisms to address exceptional
circumstances such as cancelled bills, stock mismatches, or expiry recalls.
Pharmacists and store operators are provided with an intuitive POS GUI for fast medicine searching, scanning,
batch selection, and billing.
Admins can monitor multi-store activity, manage stock transfers, configure pricing rules, and generate
regulatory reports.
