3.4 USE CASE NARRATIVES
UC-01: POS Billing
Actors: Cashier, Pharmacist (if prescription check needed)
Preconditions: Cashier logged in; POS online; product master loaded.
Main Flow:
1. Cashier scans barcode or searches medicine name.
2. System displays available batches with MRP, expiry, GST, stock.
3. Cashier selects batch and quantity — system validates stock and prescription requirement.
4. If prescription-required, system prompts Pharmacist approval (sub-flow).
5. Cashier adds items to cart; applies membership/promos if any.
6. System computes GST line-wise and invoice total.
7. Cashier selects payment mode (cash/card/UPI/credit/split).
8. On successful payment, system prints bill and optional QR label; inventory reduces batch-wise.
9. System logs transaction and updates reports.
Alternative Flows:
• A1: Insufficient stock → suggest other batch or disallow item.
• A2: Return/Cancel before payment → cart clears, no stock change.
Postconditions: Invoice created; stock updated; audit log entry made.
UC-02: Good Received Note (GRN) Processing
Actors: Store Manager / Pharmacist
Preconditions: Purchase Order (PO) created (optional); supplier invoice available.
Main Flow:
1. Create PO or select existing PO.
2. Add received items with batch number, MRP, expiry, quantity.
3. System validates item SKU and suggests HSN/GST.
4. Generate GRN; optionally print labels for batches (QR/barcode).
5. On GRN confirmation, inventory updates; supplier outstanding updated.
6. System logs GRN and links to supplier invoice.
Alternative Flows:
• Reject wrong batch → create discrepancy record and notify supplier.
UC-03: Inventory Audit and Adjustment
Actors: Store Manager, Pharmacist
Main Flow:
1. Trigger stock audit mode — generate expected stock listing by batch.
2. Perform physical count and enter actual counts.
3. System computes variances and requires reason for adjustments.
4. On approval (manager), system adjusts inventory and logs reasons.
UC-04: Stock Audit
Primary Actor: Store Manager
Success Flow:
1. Initiate audit session.
2. System generates expected batch-wise stock sheet.
3. Physical count is entered.
4. Variance generated.
5. Manager approves adjustments.
6. Inventory updated.
UC-05: Supplier Management
Flow: Add/edit supplier → Link with PO/GRN
UC-06: Reports
Flow: Select report → Apply filters → Export
UC-07: User/Store Management
Flow: Add store → Add users → Assign roles
